UNITED STATES v. SAMUEL SCHIFF & CO. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit, March 6, 1906.) No. 151 (3631). Appeal from the Circuit Court of the United States for the Southern District of New York. For decision below, see 140 Fed. 63. Charles Duane Baker, Asst. U. S. Atty. Com-stock & Washburn (Albert H. Washburn, of counsel), for appellees.

Before WALLACE, LACOMBE, and COXE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decision of Circuit Court affirmed.
